No information on a possible motive has been released.

Agerton remains jailed on a $5 million bond and faces six counts of first-degree murder.

Will County Circuit Judge Marzell Richardson upheld the bond after a public defender requested it be lowered.

Agerton was released from the Illinois Department of Corrections on November 29 after serving 15 months in jail for his fourth DUI conviction.

His deceased grandmother was a mechanic in World War II with the Women’s Army Corps, serving with a motor pool in the Pacific Theater, according to local news station 89 WLS.

